{"questionId":"9074768","questionHtml":"<p>Planet <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>X</mtext></math> and planet <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Y</mtext></math> both emit radiation as black bodies. Planet <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Y</mtext></math> has twice the surface temperature and one third of the radius of planet <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>X</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p>What is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mtext>power&nbsp;radiated&nbsp;by&nbsp;planet&nbsp;X</mtext><mtext>power&nbsp;radiated&nbsp;by&nbsp;planet&nbsp;Y</mtext></mfrac></math>?&nbsp;</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>16</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>16</mn><mn>9</mn></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074768","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.30","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Planet X and planet Y both emit radiation as black bodies. Planet Y has twice the surface temperature and one third of the radius of planet X. What is power radiated by planet Xpow","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"30","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 8: Energy production","8.2 – Thermal energy transfer","Core","Topic 8: Energy production"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}